Comparisons of testing data across countries is compromised for several reasons (see note below).
Total confirmed cases of COVID-19 per million people
Source: Tests: official data collated by Our World in Data. Confirmed cases: European CDC – Situation Update Worldwide (updated 6th April,
Note: For testing figures, there are substantial differences across countries in terms of the units, whether or not all labs are included, the extent
to which negative and pending tests are included and other aspects. Details for each country can be found at ourworldindata.org/covid-testing.
